
<div class="panel-group" id="accordion2">
  <div class="panel panel-default">
    <div class="panel-heading">
      <h4 class="panel-title">
        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseTen">Who, What, When, Where, Why, How</a>
      </h4>
    </div>
    <div id="collapseTen" class="panel-collapse collapse in">
      <div class="panel-body">
        <h4 class="headerunderline">Who</h4>
        <p>64 Teams may enter the Weekend Tournament Series WTS) of the AD2L WTS</p>
        <h4 class="headerunderline">What</h4>
        <p>The AD2L (WTS) - Captain’s Mode</p>
        <h4 class="headerunderline">When</h4>
        <p>NA: Saturdays, @5:00pm EDT. Registration begins weekly</p>
        <p>EU: Saturdays, @19.00 CEST. Registration begins weekly</p>
        <h4 class="headerunderline">Where</h4>
        <p>Check-in where you registered by clicking the ‘Check-in’ button that appears on the WTS tab <%=link_to "here", seasons_path%>, @4:45pm. <%=link_to "Affinity", "players/140"%> will be in the guild chat and <%=link_to "steam group", "steam://friends/joinchat/103582791435143521"%> to assist you.  Brackets will be built from those who check in, so make sure to check in on time!</p>
        <h4 class="headerunderline">Why</h4>
        <p>For those of us not as good as DK, we play amateur tournaments.</p>
        <h4 class="headerunderline">How</h4>
        <ol>
          <li>1. Register from your teampage or <%=link_to "here", "register"%>.  (Can be found from the <%=link_to "My Info", (@current_user ? @current_user : "players/new")%>)</li>
          <li>2. Check-in 15 minutes before the tournament from the WTS tab <%=link_to "here", seasons_path%>. </li>
          <li>3. Use the <%=link_to "steam group chat", "steam://friends/joinchat/103582791435143521"%> to find your opponent</li>
            <ol class="sublist">
              <li>a. For example, if I’m on team APE, and my opponents are Cheat Commandos, I’ll type into the chat: APE vs Cheat Commandos, join lobby ad2l123</li>
              <li>b. As a general rule, ask for a caster if you want your game on Dota TV (ticketed). Casters might be calling your team, if so, go join their lobby!</li>
            </ol>
          <li>4. The winner will type into the chat (or steam msg <%=link_to "Affinity", "players/140"%>) they won their game. </li>
          <li>5. Rinse and repeat steps 2-4 until the 1st place is yours!</li>
        <ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
